All too often, every great female rock musician has to answer a
predictable question - what is it like being a girl in a band?

For many, the sight of a girl shredding a guitar or laying into the drums
is still a bit of a novelty. As soon as women started forming their own
bands they were given labels - the rock chick, the girl band or one half
of the rock and roll couple.

Kate Mossman aims to look beyond the cliches of fallen angels, grunge
babes and rock chicks as she gets the untold stories from rock's frontline
to discover if it has always been different for the girl in a band.
